sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: cI+luxR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Promoter (lambda cI and luxR regulated -- hybrid)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
cI repressor negatively regulates this promoter and LuxR activates its transcription.The effect of cI is dominant over LuxR. This part is based on the LuxR and cI repressor regulated hybrid promoter designed and tested by Ron Weiss. It requires the binding of two cI repressor dimers for maximal repression and contains two cI repressor binding sites namely, OR1 and OR2. This promoter is leaky in the sense that 'some' transcription is seen in the absence of both cI and LuxR.

 

LuxI cI activity of promoter
+ + zero
+ - maximum
- + zero
- - leaky (no quantitative information)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part was designed based on the LuxR and cI repressor regulated hybrid promoter tested by Ron Weiss and the LuxR-LuxICDABE sequence annotated by Tom Knight AF170104.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: placIQ RBS
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: We used I14032, B0030 and K193600.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This composite part contains pLacIQ(BBa_I14032) and RBS(B0030) and melA on low copy vector(PSB4A5).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kazuaki Amikura

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0030
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Strong RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength is considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0032</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("orig" in figure 4-14 of Ron Weiss thesis).

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K193600
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The gene sequence was obtained from GENEART.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: melA is coding sequence of tyrosinase. Tyrosinase is enzyme which converts from tyrosine to dopaquinone. Dopaquinone is intermediate product of melanin biosynthesis pathway.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We added restriction enzyme sites (Prefix-Suffix) to the upstream and down stream of the ORF of melA.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kazuaki Amikura
